  "texts": [
    "Training dataIn general, the AI model requires enormous high-quality samples to train, especially when it consists of a large number of learnable parameters.",
    "However, in practice, training an AI model faces several challenges.",
    "First, the quality of training data varies with sensor and measurement noise, which may lead to the wrong or biased model that cannot learn the correct pattern of underlying systems.",
    "Second, it may be difficult for ISAC networks to obtain sufficient training samples due to data security issues in some specific scenarios.",
    "In addition, the process of collecting training samples can be time-consuming and expensive."
  ],
